23// Liftoff Frames.
24//
25// slot Frame
26// +--------------------+---------------------------
27// n+4 | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
28// n+3 | parameter n |
29// ... | ... |
30// 4 | parameter 1 | or parameter 2
31// 3 | parameter 0 | or parameter 1
32// 2 | (result address) | or parameter 0
33// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
34// 1 | return addr (ra) |
35// 0 | previous frame (fp)|
36// -----+--------------------+ <-- frame ptr (fp)
37// -1 | StackFrame::WASM |
38// -2 | instance |
39// -3 | feedback vector|
40// -----+--------------------+---------------------------
41// -4 | slot 0 | ^
42// -5 | slot 1 | |
43// | | Frame slots
44// | | |
45// | | v
46// | optional padding slot to keep the stack 16 byte aligned.
47// -----+--------------------+ <-- stack ptr (sp)
48//
49
50inline MemOperand GetStackSlot(int offset) { return MemOperand(fp, -offset); }
51
52inline MemOperand GetInstanceDataOperand() {
53 return GetStackSlot(WasmLiftoffFrameConstants::kInstanceDataOffset);
54}
55
56template <typename T>
57inline MemOperand GetMemOp(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register addr,
58 Register offset, T offset_imm,
59 bool i64_offset = false, unsigned shift_amount = 0) {
60 if (offset != no_reg) {
61 if (!i64_offset) {
62 assm->bstrpick_d(kScratchReg, offset, 31, 0);
63 offset = kScratchReg;
64 }
65 if (shift_amount != 0) {
66 assm->alsl_d(kScratchReg, offset, addr, shift_amount);
67 } else {
68 assm->add_d(kScratchReg, offset, addr);
69 }
70 addr = kScratchReg;
71 }
72 if (is_int31(offset_imm)) {
73 int32_t offset_imm32 = static_cast<int32_t>(offset_imm);
74 return MemOperand(addr, offset_imm32);
75 } else {
76 assm->li(kScratchReg2, Operand(offset_imm));
77 assm->add_d(kScratchReg2, addr, kScratchReg2);
78 return MemOperand(kScratchReg2, 0);
79 }
80}

82inline void Load(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister dst, MemOperand src,
83 ValueKind kind) {
84 switch (kind) {
85 case kI16:
86 assm->Ld_h(dst.gp(), src);
87 break;
88 case kI32:
89 assm->Ld_w(dst.gp(), src);
90 break;
91 case kI64:
92 case kRef:
93 case kRefNull:
94 case kRtt:
95 assm->Ld_d(dst.gp(), src);
96 break;
97 case kF32:
98 assm->Fld_s(dst.fp(), src);
99 break;
100 case kF64:
101 assm->Fld_d(dst.fp(), src);
102 break;
103 case kS128:
104 UNREACHABLE();
105 break;
106 default:
107 UNREACHABLE();
108 }
109}
110
111inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst, LiftoffRegister src,
112 ValueKind kind) {
113 switch (kind) {
114 case kI16:
115 assm->St_h(src.gp(), dst);
116 break;
117 case kI32:
118 assm->St_w(src.gp(), dst);
119 break;
120 case kI64:
121 case kRefNull:
122 case kRef:
123 case kRtt:
124 assm->St_d(src.gp(), dst);
125 break;
126 case kF32:
127 assm->Fst_s(src.fp(), dst);
128 break;
129 case kF64:
130 assm->Fst_d(src.fp(), dst);
131 break;
132 default:
133 UNREACHABLE();
134 }
135}

137inline void Store(LiftoffAssembler* assm, Register base, int32_t offset,
138 LiftoffRegister src, ValueKind kind) {
139 MemOperand dst(base, offset);
140 Store(assm, dst, src, kind);
141}
142
143inline void push(LiftoffAssembler* assm, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
144 switch (kind) {
145 case kI32:
146 assm->addi_d(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
147 assm->St_w(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
148 break;
149 case kI64:
150 case kRefNull:
151 case kRef:
152 case kRtt:
153 assm->Push(reg.gp());
154 break;
155 case kF32:
156 assm->addi_d(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
157 assm->Fst_s(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
158 break;
159 case kF64:
160 assm->addi_d(sp, sp, -kSystemPointerSize);
161 assm->Fst_d(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, 0));
162 break;
163 case kS128:
164 UNREACHABLE();
165 break;
166 default:
167 UNREACHABLE();
168 }
169}
170
171inline void StoreToMemory(LiftoffAssembler* assm, MemOperand dst,
172 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src) {
173 if (src.is_reg()) {
174 Store(assm, dst, src.reg(), src.kind());
175 return;
176 }
177
178 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(assm);
179 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
180 if (src.is_const()) {
181 if (src.i32_const() == 0) {
182 temp = zero_reg;
183 } else {
184 assm->li(temp, static_cast<int64_t>(src.i32_const()));
185 }
186 } else {
187 DCHECK(src.is_stack());
188 if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
189 assm->Ld_w(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
190 } else {
191 assm->Ld_d(temp, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src.offset()));
192 }
193 }
194
195 if (value_kind_size(src.kind()) == 4) {
196 assm->St_w(temp, dst);
197 } else {
198 DCHECK_EQ(8, value_kind_size(src.kind()));
199 assm->St_d(temp, dst);
200 }
201}

205int LiftoffAssembler::PrepareStackFrame() {
206 int offset = pc_offset();
207 // When constant that represents size of stack frame can't be represented
208 // as 16bit we need three instructions to add it to sp, so we reserve space
209 // for this case.
210 addi_d(sp, sp, 0);
211 nop();
212 nop();
213 return offset;
214}
215
216void LiftoffAssembler::CallFrameSetupStub(int declared_function_index) {
217// The standard library used by gcc tryjobs does not consider `std::find` to be
218// `constexpr`, so wrap it in a `#ifdef __clang__` block.
219#ifdef __clang__
220 static_assert(std::find(std::begin(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
221 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters),
222 kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg) ==
223 std::end(wasm::kGpParamRegisters));
224#endif
225
226 // On LOONG64, we must push at least {ra} before calling the stub, otherwise
227 // it would get clobbered with no possibility to recover it. So just set
228 // up the frame here.
229 EnterFrame(StackFrame::WASM);
230 LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister(kLiftoffFrameSetupFunctionReg),
231 WasmValue(declared_function_index));
232 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmLiftoffFrameSetup);
233}
234
235void LiftoffAssembler::PrepareTailCall(int num_callee_stack_params,
236 int stack_param_delta) {
237 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
238 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
239
240 // Push the return address and frame pointer to complete the stack frame.
241 Ld_d(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 8));
242 Push(scratch);
243 Ld_d(scratch, MemOperand(fp, 0));
244 Push(scratch);
245
246 // Shift the whole frame upwards.
247 int slot_count = num_callee_stack_params + 2;
248 for (int i = slot_count - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
249 Ld_d(scratch, MemOperand(sp, i * 8));
250 St_d(scratch, MemOperand(fp, (i - stack_param_delta) * 8));
251 }
252
253 // Set the new stack and frame pointer.
254 addi_d(sp, fp, -stack_param_delta * 8);
255 Pop(ra, fp);
256}

260void LiftoffAssembler::PatchPrepareStackFrame(
261 int offset, SafepointTableBuilder* safepoint_table_builder,
262 bool feedback_vector_slot, size_t stack_param_slots) {
263 // The frame_size includes the frame marker and the instance slot. Both are
264 // pushed as part of frame construction, so we don't need to allocate memory
265 // for them anymore.
266 int frame_size = GetTotalFrameSize() - 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
267 // The frame setup builtin also pushes the feedback vector.
268 if (feedback_vector_slot) {
269 frame_size -= kSystemPointerSize;
270 }
271
272 // We can't run out of space, just pass anything big enough to not cause the
273 // assembler to try to grow the buffer.
274 constexpr int kAvailableSpace = 256;
275 MacroAssembler patching_assembler(
276 nullptr, AssemblerOptions{}, CodeObjectRequired::kNo,
277 ExternalAssemblerBuffer(buffer_start_ + offset, kAvailableSpace));
278
279 if (V8_LIKELY(frame_size < 4 * KB)) {
280 // This is the standard case for small frames: just subtract from SP and be
281 // done with it.
282 patching_assembler.Add_d(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
283 return;
284 }
285
286 // The frame size is bigger than 4KB, so we might overflow the available stack
287 // space if we first allocate the frame and then do the stack check (we will
288 // need some remaining stack space for throwing the exception). That's why we
289 // check the available stack space before we allocate the frame. To do this we
290 // replace the {__ Add_d(sp, sp, -frame_size)} with a jump to OOL code that
291 // does this "extended stack check".
292 //
293 // The OOL code can simply be generated here with the normal assembler,
294 // because all other code generation, including OOL code, has already finished
295 // when {PatchPrepareStackFrame} is called. The function prologue then jumps
296 // to the current {pc_offset()} to execute the OOL code for allocating the
297 // large frame.
298 // Emit the unconditional branch in the function prologue (from {offset} to
299 // {pc_offset()}).
300
301 int imm32 = pc_offset() - offset;
302 CHECK(is_int26(imm32));
303 patching_assembler.b(imm32 >> 2);
304
305 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
306 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
307 // check in the condition code.
308 RecordComment("OOL: stack check for large frame");
309 Label continuation;
310 if (frame_size < v8_flags.stack_size * 1024) {
311 Register stack_limit = kScratchReg;
312 LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
313 Add_d(stack_limit, stack_limit, Operand(frame_size));
314 Branch(&continuation, uge, sp, Operand(stack_limit));
315 }
316
317 if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
318 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
319 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
320 regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
321 for (auto reg : kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
322 for (auto reg : kFpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
323 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
324 li(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(), frame_size);
325 Add_d(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
326 Operand(stack_param_slots * kStackSlotSize +
327 CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
328 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
329 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
330 } else {
331 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
332 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
333 // The call will not return; just define an empty safepoint.
334 safepoint_table_builder->DefineSafepoint(this);
335 if (v8_flags.debug_code) stop();
336 }
337
338 bind(&continuation);
339
340 // Now allocate the stack space. Note that this might do more than just
341 // decrementing the SP;
342 Add_d(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_size));
343
344 // Jump back to the start of the function, from {pc_offset()} to
345 // right after the reserved space for the {__ Add_d(sp, sp, -framesize)}
346 // (which is a Branch now).
347 int func_start_offset = offset + 3 * kInstrSize;
348 imm32 = func_start_offset - pc_offset();
349 CHECK(is_int26(imm32));
350 b(imm32 >> 2);
351}

375void LiftoffAssembler::CheckTierUp(int declared_func_index, int budget_used,
376 Label* ool_label,
377 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
378 Register budget_array = kScratchReg;
379
380 Register instance_data = cache_state_.cached_instance_data;
381 if (instance_data == no_reg) {
382 instance_data = budget_array; // Reuse the scratch register.
383 LoadInstanceDataFromFrame(instance_data);
384 }
385
386 constexpr int kArrayOffset = wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(
387 WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTieringBudgetArrayOffset);
388 Ld_d(budget_array, MemOperand(instance_data, kArrayOffset));
389
390 int budget_arr_offset = kInt32Size * declared_func_index;
391
392 Register budget = kScratchReg2;
393 MemOperand budget_addr(budget_array, budget_arr_offset);
394 Ld_w(budget, budget_addr);
395 Sub_w(budget, budget, budget_used);
396 St_w(budget, budget_addr);
397
398 Branch(ool_label, less, budget, Operand(zero_reg));
399}
400
401Register LiftoffAssembler::LoadOldFramePointer() {
402 if (!v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
403 return fp;
404 }
405
406 LiftoffRegister old_fp = GetUnusedRegister(RegClass::kGpReg, {});
407 Label done, call_runtime;
408 Ld_d(old_fp.gp(), MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
409 BranchShort(
410 &call_runtime, eq, old_fp.gp(),
411 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
412 mov(old_fp.gp(), fp);
413 jmp(&done);
414
415 bind(&call_runtime);
416 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save = cache_state()->used_registers;
417 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
418 li(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
419 PrepareCallCFunction(1, kScratchReg);
420 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_load_old_fp(), 1);
421 if (old_fp.gp() != kReturnRegister0) {
422 mov(old_fp.gp(), kReturnRegister0);
423 }
424 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
425
426 bind(&done);
427 return old_fp.gp();
428}

430void LiftoffAssembler::CheckStackShrink() {
431 Label done;
432 {
433 UseScratchRegisterScope temps{this};
434 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
435 Ld_d(scratch, MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
436 BranchShort(
437 &done, ne, scratch,
438 Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
439 }
440 LiftoffRegList regs_to_save;
441 for (auto reg : kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
442 for (auto reg : kFpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
443 PushRegisters(regs_to_save);
444 li(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
445 PrepareCallCFunction(1, kScratchReg);
446 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
447 mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
448 PopRegisters(regs_to_save);
449 bind(&done);
450}

452void LiftoffAssembler::LoadConstant(LiftoffRegister reg, WasmValue value) {
453 switch (value.type().kind()) {
454 case kI32:
455 MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i32()));
456 break;
457 case kI64:
458 MacroAssembler::li(reg.gp(), Operand(value.to_i64()));
459 break;
460 case kF32:
461 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f32_boxed().get_bits());
462 break;
463 case kF64:
464 MacroAssembler::Move(reg.fp(), value.to_f64_boxed().get_bits());
465 break;
466 default:
467 UNREACHABLE();
468 }
469}

481void LiftoffAssembler::LoadFromInstance(Register dst, Register instance,
482 int offset, int size) {
483 DCHECK_LE(0, offset);
484 switch (size) {
485 case 1:
486 Ld_b(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
487 break;
488 case 4:
489 Ld_w(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
490 break;
491 case 8:
492 Ld_d(dst, MemOperand(instance, offset));
493 break;
494 default:
495 UNIMPLEMENTED();
496 }

511void LiftoffAssembler::LoadTaggedPointer(Register dst, Register src_addr,
512 Register offset_reg,
513 int32_t offset_imm,
514 uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
515 bool needs_shift) {
516 unsigned shift_amount = !needs_shift ? 0 : COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 2 : 3;
517 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
518 false, shift_amount);
519 LoadTaggedField(dst, src_op);
520
521 // Since LoadTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
522 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
523 // calling it.
524 // In case of compressed pointers, there is an additional instruction
525 // (pointer decompression) after the load.
526 uint8_t protected_instruction_offset_bias =
527 COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? 2 * kInstrSize : kInstrSize;
528 if (protected_load_pc) {
529 *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - protected_instruction_offset_bias;
530 }
531}

534 int32_t offset_imm) {
535 LoadProtectedPointerField(dst, MemOperand{src_addr, offset_imm});
536}

554void LiftoffAssembler::StoreTaggedPointer(Register dst_addr,
555 Register offset_reg,
556 int32_t offset_imm, Register src,
557 LiftoffRegList pinned,
558 uint32_t* protected_store_pc,
559 SkipWriteBarrier skip_write_barrier) {
560 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
561 Operand offset_op =
562 offset_reg.is_valid() ? Operand(offset_reg) : Operand(offset_imm);
563 // For the write barrier (below), we cannot have both an offset register and
564 // an immediate offset. Add them to a 32-bit offset initially, but in a 64-bit
565 // register, because that's needed in the MemOperand below.
566 if (offset_reg.is_valid() && offset_imm) {
567 Register effective_offset = temps.Acquire();
568 Add_d(effective_offset, offset_reg, Operand(offset_imm));
569 offset_op = Operand(effective_offset);
570 }
571
572 if (offset_op.is_reg()) {
573 StoreTaggedField(src, MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_op.rm()));
574 } else {
575 StoreTaggedField(src, MemOperand(dst_addr, offset_imm));
576 }
577
578 // Since StoreTaggedField might start with an instruction loading an immediate
579 // argument to a register, we have to compute the {protected_load_pc} after
580 // calling it.
581 if (protected_store_pc) {
582 *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
583 }
584
585 if (skip_write_barrier || v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) return;
586
587 Label exit;
588 CheckPageFlag(dst_addr, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
589 kZero, &exit);
590 JumpIfSmi(src, &exit);
591 CheckPageFlag(src, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &exit);
592 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(dst_addr, offset_op, SaveFPRegsMode::kSave,
593 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
594 bind(&exit);
595}
596
597void LiftoffAssembler::Load(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
598 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
599 LoadType type, uint32_t* protected_load_pc,
600 bool is_load_mem, bool i64_offset,
601 bool needs_shift) {
602 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
603 unsigned shift_amount = needs_shift ? type.size_log_2() : 0;
604 MemOperand src_op = liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm,
605 i64_offset, shift_amount);
606
607 switch (type.value()) {
608 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
609 case LoadType::kI64Load8U:
610 Ld_bu(dst.gp(), src_op);
611 break;
612 case LoadType::kI32Load8S:
613 case LoadType::kI64Load8S:
614 Ld_b(dst.gp(), src_op);
615 break;
616 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
617 case LoadType::kI64Load16U:
618 MacroAssembler::Ld_hu(dst.gp(), src_op);
619 break;
620 case LoadType::kI32Load16S:
621 case LoadType::kI64Load16S:
622 MacroAssembler::Ld_h(dst.gp(), src_op);
623 break;
624 case LoadType::kI64Load32U:
625 MacroAssembler::Ld_wu(dst.gp(), src_op);
626 break;
627 case LoadType::kI32Load:
628 case LoadType::kI64Load32S:
629 MacroAssembler::Ld_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
630 break;
631 case LoadType::kI64Load:
632 MacroAssembler::Ld_d(dst.gp(), src_op);
633 break;
634 case LoadType::kF32Load:
635 MacroAssembler::Fld_s(dst.fp(), src_op);
636 break;
637 case LoadType::kF32LoadF16:
638 UNIMPLEMENTED();
639 break;
640 case LoadType::kF64Load:
641 MacroAssembler::Fld_d(dst.fp(), src_op);
642 break;
643 case LoadType::kS128Load:
644 UNREACHABLE();
645 break;
646 default:
647 UNREACHABLE();
648 }
649 // protected_load_pc should be the address of the load/store instruction.
650 // The MacroAssembler load/store may contain some instructions for adjusting
651 // MemOperand, so use pc_offset - kInstrSize to locate.
652 if (protected_load_pc) *protected_load_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
653}
654
655void LiftoffAssembler::Store(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
656 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
657 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
658 uint32_t* protected_store_pc, bool is_store_mem,
659 bool i64_offset) {
660 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
661 MemOperand dst_op =
662 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
663
664 switch (type.value()) {
665 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
666 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
667 St_b(src.gp(), dst_op);
668 break;
669 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
670 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
671 MacroAssembler::St_h(src.gp(), dst_op);
672 break;
673 case StoreType::kI32Store:
674 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
675 MacroAssembler::St_w(src.gp(), dst_op);
676 break;
677 case StoreType::kI64Store:
678 MacroAssembler::St_d(src.gp(), dst_op);
679 break;
680 case StoreType::kF32Store:
681 MacroAssembler::Fst_s(src.fp(), dst_op);
682 break;
683 case StoreType::kF32StoreF16:
684 UNIMPLEMENTED();
685 break;
686 case StoreType::kF64Store:
687 MacroAssembler::Fst_d(src.fp(), dst_op);
688 break;
689 case StoreType::kS128Store:
690 UNREACHABLE();
691 break;
692 default:
693 UNREACHABLE();
694 }
695 // protected_store_pc should be the address of the load/store instruction.
696 // The MacroAssembler load/store may contain some instructions for adjusting
697 // MemOperand, so use pc_offset - kInstrSize to locate.
698 if (protected_store_pc) *protected_store_pc = pc_offset() - kInstrSize;
699}
700
701void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicLoad(LiftoffRegister dst, Register src_addr,
702 Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
703 LoadType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
704 bool i64_offset) {
705 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
706 MemOperand src_op =
707 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, src_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
708 switch (type.value()) {
709 case LoadType::kI32Load8U:
710 case LoadType::kI64Load8U: {
711 Ld_bu(dst.gp(), src_op);
712 dbar(0);
713 return;
714 }
715 case LoadType::kI32Load16U:
716 case LoadType::kI64Load16U: {
717 Ld_hu(dst.gp(), src_op);
718 dbar(0);
719 return;
720 }
721 case LoadType::kI32Load: {
722 Ld_w(dst.gp(), src_op);
723 dbar(0);
724 return;
725 }
726 case LoadType::kI64Load32U: {
727 Ld_wu(dst.gp(), src_op);
728 dbar(0);
729 return;
730 }
731 case LoadType::kI64Load: {
732 Ld_d(dst.gp(), src_op);
733 dbar(0);
734 return;
735 }
736 default:
737 UNREACHABLE();
738 }
739}

741void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicStore(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
742 uintptr_t offset_imm, LiftoffRegister src,
743 StoreType type, LiftoffRegList pinned,
744 bool i64_offset) {
745 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
746 MemOperand dst_op =
747 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
748 switch (type.value()) {
749 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
750 case StoreType::kI32Store8: {
751 dbar(0);
752 St_b(src.gp(), dst_op);
753 return;
754 }
755 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
756 case StoreType::kI32Store16: {
757 dbar(0);
758 St_h(src.gp(), dst_op);
759 return;
760 }
761 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
762 case StoreType::kI32Store: {
763 dbar(0);
764 St_w(src.gp(), dst_op);
765 return;
766 }
767 case StoreType::kI64Store: {
768 dbar(0);
769 St_d(src.gp(), dst_op);
770 return;
771 }
772 default:
773 UNREACHABLE();
774 }

777#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(load_linked, store_conditional, size, \
778 bin_instr, aligned) \
779 do { \
780 Label binop; \
781 andi(temp3, temp0, aligned); \
782 Sub_d(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp3)); \
783 slli_w(temp3, temp3, 3); \
784 dbar(0); \
785 bind(&binop); \
786 load_linked(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
787 ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp1, temp3, size, false); \
788 bin_instr(temp2, result.gp(), Operand(value.gp())); \
789 InsertBits(temp1, temp2, temp3, size); \
790 store_conditional(temp1, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
791 BranchShort(&binop, eq, temp1, Operand(zero_reg)); \
792 dbar(0); \
793 } while (0)
794
795#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(name, inst32, inst64, opcode) \
796 void LiftoffAssembler::Atomic##name( \
797 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm, \
798 LiftoffRegister value, LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type, \
799 bool i64_offset) { \
800 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, value, result}; \
801 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg); \
802 Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
803 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
804 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
805 Register temp3 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp(); \
806 MemOperand dst_op = \
807 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset); \
808 Add_d(temp0, dst_op.base(), dst_op.offset()); \
809 switch (type.value()) { \
810 case StoreType::kI64Store8: \
811 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 8, inst64, 7); \
812 break; \
813 case StoreType::kI32Store8: \
814 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll_w, Sc_w, 8, inst32, 3); \
815 break; \
816 case StoreType::kI64Store16: \
817 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 16, inst64, 7); \
818 break; \
819 case StoreType::kI32Store16: \
820 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll_w, Sc_w, 16, inst32, 3); \
821 break; \
822 case StoreType::kI64Store32: \
823 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 32, inst64, 7); \
824 break; \
825 case StoreType::kI32Store: \
826 am##opcode##_db_w(result.gp(), value.gp(), temp0); \
827 break; \
828 case StoreType::kI64Store: \
829 am##opcode##_db_d(result.gp(), value.gp(), temp0); \
830 break; \
831 default: \
832 UNREACHABLE(); \
833 } \
834 }

836ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Add, Add_w, Add_d, add)
837ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(And, And, And, and)
838ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, Or, Or, or)
839ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, Xor, Xor, xor)

896#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(load_linked, store_conditional, \

913void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicExchange(Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg,
914 uintptr_t offset_imm,

916 LiftoffRegister result, StoreType type,

921 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
922 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
923 MemOperand dst_op =
924 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
925 Add_d(temp0, dst_op.base(), dst_op.offset());
926 switch (type.value()) {
927 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
928 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 8, 7);

930 case StoreType::kI32Store8:

932 break;
933 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
934 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 16, 7);
935 break;
936 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
937 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_w, Sc_w, 16, 3);
938 break;

954#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, \
955 store_conditional) \
956 do { \
957 Label compareExchange; \
958 Label exit; \
959 dbar(0); \
960 bind(&compareExchange); \
961 load_linked(result.gp(), MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
962 BranchShort(&exit, ne, expected.gp(), Operand(result.gp())); \
963 mov(temp2, new_value.gp()); \
964 store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
965 BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
966 bind(&exit); \
967 dbar(0); \
968 } while (0)
969
970#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT( \
971 load_linked, store_conditional, size, aligned) \
972 do { \
973 Label compareExchange; \
974 Label exit; \
975 andi(temp1, temp0, aligned); \
976 Sub_d(temp0, temp0, Operand(temp1)); \
977 slli_w(temp1, temp1, 3); \
978 dbar(0); \
979 bind(&compareExchange); \
980 load_linked(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
981 ExtractBits(result.gp(), temp2, temp1, size, false); \
982 ExtractBits(temp2, expected.gp(), zero_reg, size, false); \
983 BranchShort(&exit, ne, temp2, Operand(result.gp())); \
984 InsertBits(temp2, new_value.gp(), temp1, size); \
985 store_conditional(temp2, MemOperand(temp0, 0)); \
986 BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, temp2, Operand(zero_reg)); \
987 bind(&exit); \
988 dbar(0); \
989 } while (0)

991void LiftoffAssembler::AtomicCompareExchange(
992 Register dst_addr, Register offset_reg, uintptr_t offset_imm,
993 LiftoffRegister expected, LiftoffRegister new_value, LiftoffRegister result,
994 StoreType type, bool i64_offset) {
995 LiftoffRegList pinned{dst_addr, expected, new_value, result};
996 if (offset_reg != no_reg) pinned.set(offset_reg);
997 Register temp0 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
998 Register temp1 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
999 Register temp2 = pinned.set(GetUnusedRegister(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
1000 MemOperand dst_op =
1001 liftoff::GetMemOp(this, dst_addr, offset_reg, offset_imm, i64_offset);
1002 Add_d(temp0, dst_op.base(), dst_op.offset());
1003 switch (type.value()) {
1004 case StoreType::kI64Store8:
1005 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 8, 7);
1006 break;
1007 case StoreType::kI32Store8:
1008 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_w, Sc_w, 8, 3);
1009 break;
1010 case StoreType::kI64Store16:
1011 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 16, 7);
1012 break;
1013 case StoreType::kI32Store16:
1014 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_w, Sc_w, 16, 3);
1015 break;
1016 case StoreType::kI64Store32:
1017 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT(Ll_d, Sc_d, 32, 7);
1018 break;
1019 case StoreType::kI32Store:
1020 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Ll_w, Sc_w);
1021 break;
1022 case StoreType::kI64Store:
1023 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(Ll_d, Sc_d);
1024 break;
1025 default:
1026 UNREACHABLE();
1027 }
1028}

1030#undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT

1054void LiftoffAssembler::MoveStackValue(uint32_t dst_offset, uint32_t src_offset,
1055 ValueKind kind) {
1056 DCHECK_NE(dst_offset, src_offset);
1057 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1058 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1059
1060 switch (kind) {
1061 case kI32:
1062 case kF32:
1063 Ld_w(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1064 St_w(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1065 break;
1066 case kI64:
1067 case kRefNull:
1068 case kRef:
1069 case kRtt:
1070 case kF64:
1071 Ld_d(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(src_offset));
1072 St_d(scratch, liftoff::GetStackSlot(dst_offset));
1073 break;
1074 case kS128:
1075 default:
1076 UNREACHABLE();
1077 }
1078}

1081 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1082 // TODO(ksreten): Handle different sizes here.
1083 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1084}

1087 ValueKind kind) {

1090 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, src);
1091 } else {
1092 UNREACHABLE();
1093 }
1094}

1096void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, LiftoffRegister reg, ValueKind kind) {
1097 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1098 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1099 switch (kind) {
1100 case kI32:
1101 St_w(reg.gp(), dst);
1102 break;
1103 case kI64:
1104 case kRef:
1105 case kRefNull:
1106 case kRtt:
1107 St_d(reg.gp(), dst);
1108 break;
1109 case kF32:
1110 Fst_s(reg.fp(), dst);
1111 break;
1112 case kF64:
1113 MacroAssembler::Fst_d(reg.fp(), dst);
1114 break;
1115 case kS128:
1116 UNREACHABLE();
1117 break;
1118 default:
1119 UNREACHABLE();
1120 }
1121}
1122
1123void LiftoffAssembler::Spill(int offset, WasmValue value) {
1124 RecordUsedSpillOffset(offset);
1125 MemOperand dst = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1126 switch (value.type().kind()) {
1127 case kI32: {
1128 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1129 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1130 MacroAssembler::li(scratch, Operand(value.to_i32()));
1131 St_w(scratch, dst);
1132 break;
1133 }
1134 case kI64:
1135 case kRef:
1136 case kRefNull: {
1137 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1138 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1139 MacroAssembler::li(scratch, value.to_i64());
1140 St_d(scratch, dst);
1141 break;
1142 }
1143 default:
1144 // kWasmF32 and kWasmF64 are unreachable, since those
1145 // constants are not tracked.
1146 UNREACHABLE();
1147 }
1148}
1149
1150void LiftoffAssembler::Fill(LiftoffRegister reg, int offset, ValueKind kind) {
1151 MemOperand src = liftoff::GetStackSlot(offset);
1152 switch (kind) {
1153 case kI32:
1154 Ld_w(reg.gp(), src);
1155 break;
1156 case kI64:
1157 case kRef:
1158 case kRefNull:
1159 // TODO(LOONG_dev): LOONG64 Check, MIPS64 dosn't need, ARM64/LOONG64 need?
1160 case kRtt:
1161 Ld_d(reg.gp(), src);
1162 break;
1163 case kF32:
1164 Fld_s(reg.fp(), src);
1165 break;
1166 case kF64:
1167 MacroAssembler::Fld_d(reg.fp(), src);
1168 break;
1169 case kS128:
1170 UNREACHABLE();
1171 break;
1172 default:
1173 UNREACHABLE();
1174 }
1175}

1180
1181void LiftoffAssembler::FillStackSlotsWithZero(int start, int size) {
1182 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
1183 RecordUsedSpillOffset(start + size);
1184
1185 if (size <= 12 * kStackSlotSize) {
1186 // Special straight-line code for up to 12 slots. Generates one
1187 // instruction per slot (<= 12 instructions total).
1188 uint32_t remainder = size;
1189 for (; remainder >= kStackSlotSize; remainder -= kStackSlotSize) {
1190 St_d(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1191 }
1192 DCHECK(remainder == 4 || remainder == 0);
1193 if (remainder) {
1194 St_w(zero_reg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(start + remainder));
1195 }
1196 } else {
1197 // General case for bigger counts (12 instructions).
1198 // Use a0 for start address (inclusive), a1 for end address (exclusive).
1199 Push(a1, a0);
1200 Add_d(a0, fp, Operand(-start - size));
1201 Add_d(a1, fp, Operand(-start));
1202
1203 Label loop;
1204 bind(&loop);
1205 St_d(zero_reg, MemOperand(a0, 0));
1206 addi_d(a0, a0, kSystemPointerSize);
1207 BranchShort(&loop, ne, a0, Operand(a1));
1208
1209 Pop(a1, a0);
1210 }
1211}

1214 ValueKind /* kind */) {
1215 Sub_d(dst, fp, Operand(offset));
1216}

1231
1232void LiftoffAssembler::IncrementSmi(LiftoffRegister dst, int offset) {
1233 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1234 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1235 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1236 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1237 Ld_w(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1238 Add_w(scratch, scratch, Operand(Smi::FromInt(1)));
1239 St_w(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1240 } else {
1241 SmiUntag(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1242 Add_d(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
1243 SmiTag(scratch);
1244 St_d(scratch, MemOperand(dst.gp(), offset));
1245 }
1246}
1247
1248void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_mul(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs) {
1249 MacroAssembler::Mul_w(dst, lhs, rhs);
1250}
1251
1252void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divs(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1253 Label* trap_div_by_zero,
1254 Label* trap_div_unrepresentable) {
1255 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_by_zero, eq, rhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1256
1257 // Check if lhs == kMinInt and rhs == -1, since this case is unrepresentable.
1258 rotri_w(kScratchReg, lhs, 31);
1259 xori(kScratchReg, kScratchReg, 1);
1260 // If lhs == kMinInt, move rhs to kScratchReg.
1261 masknez(kScratchReg, rhs, kScratchReg);
1262 addi_w(kScratchReg, kScratchReg, 1);
1263 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_unrepresentable, eq, kScratchReg,
1264 Operand(zero_reg));
1265
1266 MacroAssembler::Div_w(dst, lhs, rhs);
1267}

1269void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_divu(Register dst, Register lhs, Register rhs,
1270 Label* trap_div_by_zero) {
1271 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap_div_by_zero, eq, rhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1272 MacroAssembler::Div_wu(dst, lhs, rhs);
1273}

1360
1361void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i64_muli(LiftoffRegister dst, LiftoffRegister lhs,
1362 int32_t imm) {
1363 if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(imm)) {
1364 emit_i64_shli(dst, lhs, base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(imm));
1365 return;
1366 }
1367 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1368 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1369 MacroAssembler::li(scratch, Operand(imm));
1370 MacroAssembler::Mul_d(dst.gp(), lhs.gp(), scratch);
1371}

1386 Operand(zero_reg));

1389 return true;
1390}

1576
1577bool LiftoffAssembler::emit_type_conversion(WasmOpcode opcode,
1578 LiftoffRegister dst,
1579 LiftoffRegister src, Label* trap) {
1580 switch (opcode) {
1581 case kExprI32ConvertI64:
1582 MacroAssembler::bstrpick_w(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 31, 0);
1583 return true;
1584 case kExprI32SConvertF32: {
1585 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1586 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1587 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1588
1589 // Real conversion.
1590 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1591 ftintrz_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1592 movfr2gr_s(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1593 // Avoid INT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT32_MIN instead,
1594 // because INT32_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1595 MacroAssembler::Add_w(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1596 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1597 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1598
1599 // Checking if trap.
1600 movgr2fr_w(kScratchDoubleReg, dst.gp());
1601 ffint_s_w(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1602 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1603 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1604 return true;
1605 }
1606 case kExprI32UConvertF32: {
1607 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1608 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1609 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1610
1611 // Real conversion.
1612 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1613 MacroAssembler::Ftintrz_uw_s(dst.gp(), rounded.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1614 // Avoid UINT32_MAX as an overflow indicator and use 0 instead,
1615 // because 0 allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1616 MacroAssembler::Add_w(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1617 MacroAssembler::Movz(dst.gp(), zero_reg, kScratchReg);
1618
1619 // Checking if trap.
1620 MacroAssembler::Ffint_d_uw(converted_back.fp(), dst.gp());
1621 fcvt_s_d(converted_back.fp(), converted_back.fp());
1622 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1623 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1624 return true;
1625 }
1626 case kExprI32SConvertF64: {
1627 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1628 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1629 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1630
1631 // Real conversion.
1632 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1633 ftintrz_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1634 movfr2gr_s(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1635
1636 // Checking if trap.
1637 ffint_d_w(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1638 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1639 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1640 return true;
1641 }
1642 case kExprI32UConvertF64: {
1643 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1644 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1645 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1646
1647 // Real conversion.
1648 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1649 MacroAssembler::Ftintrz_uw_d(dst.gp(), rounded.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1650
1651 // Checking if trap.
1652 MacroAssembler::Ffint_d_uw(converted_back.fp(), dst.gp());
1653 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1654 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1655 return true;
1656 }
1657 case kExprI32ReinterpretF32:
1658 MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1659 return true;
1660 case kExprI64SConvertI32:
1661 slli_w(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 0);
1662 return true;
1663 case kExprI64UConvertI32:
1664 MacroAssembler::bstrpick_d(dst.gp(), src.gp(), 31, 0);
1665 return true;
1666 case kExprI64SConvertF32: {
1667 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1668 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1669 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1670
1671 // Real conversion.
1672 MacroAssembler::Trunc_s(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1673 ftintrz_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1674 movfr2gr_d(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1675 // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1676 // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1677 MacroAssembler::Add_d(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1678 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1679 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1680
1681 // Checking if trap.
1682 movgr2fr_d(kScratchDoubleReg, dst.gp());
1683 ffint_s_l(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1684 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1685 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1686 return true;
1687 }
1688 case kExprI64UConvertF32: {
1689 // Real conversion.
1690 MacroAssembler::Ftintrz_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1691 kScratchReg);
1692
1693 // Checking if trap.
1694 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1695 return true;
1696 }
1697 case kExprI64SConvertF64: {
1698 LiftoffRegister rounded = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src});
1699 LiftoffRegister converted_back =
1700 GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{src, rounded});
1701
1702 // Real conversion.
1703 MacroAssembler::Trunc_d(rounded.fp(), src.fp());
1704 ftintrz_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, rounded.fp());
1705 movfr2gr_d(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1706 // Avoid INT64_MAX as an overflow indicator and use INT64_MIN instead,
1707 // because INT64_MIN allows easier out-of-bounds detection.
1708 MacroAssembler::Add_d(kScratchReg, dst.gp(), 1);
1709 MacroAssembler::Slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, dst.gp());
1710 MacroAssembler::Movn(dst.gp(), kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
1711
1712 // Checking if trap.
1713 movgr2fr_d(kScratchDoubleReg, dst.gp());
1714 ffint_d_l(converted_back.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1715 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(rounded.fp(), converted_back.fp(), CEQ);
1716 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(trap);
1717 return true;
1718 }
1719 case kExprI64UConvertF64: {
1720 // Real conversion.
1721 MacroAssembler::Ftintrz_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg,
1722 kScratchReg);
1723
1724 // Checking if trap.
1725 MacroAssembler::Branch(trap, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
1726 return true;
1727 }
1728 case kExprI64ReinterpretF64:
1729 movfr2gr_d(dst.gp(), src.fp());
1730 return true;
1731 case kExprF32SConvertI32: {
1732 LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1733 movgr2fr_w(scratch.fp(), src.gp());
1734 ffint_s_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1735 return true;
1736 }
1737 case kExprF32UConvertI32:
1738 MacroAssembler::Ffint_s_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1739 return true;
1740 case kExprF32ConvertF64:
1741 fcvt_s_d(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1742 return true;
1743 case kExprF32ReinterpretI32:
1744 MacroAssembler::FmoveLow(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1745 return true;
1746 case kExprF64SConvertI32: {
1747 LiftoffRegister scratch = GetUnusedRegister(kFpReg, LiftoffRegList{dst});
1748 movgr2fr_w(scratch.fp(), src.gp());
1749 ffint_d_w(dst.fp(), scratch.fp());
1750 return true;
1751 }
1752 case kExprF64UConvertI32:
1753 MacroAssembler::Ffint_d_uw(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1754 return true;
1755 case kExprF64ConvertF32:
1756 fcvt_d_s(dst.fp(), src.fp());
1757 return true;
1758 case kExprF64ReinterpretI64:
1759 movgr2fr_d(dst.fp(), src.gp());
1760 return true;
1761 case kExprI32SConvertSatF32:
1762 ftintrz_w_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1763 movfr2gr_s(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1764 return true;
1765 case kExprI32UConvertSatF32: {
1766 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1767 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1768 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1769 CompareF32(src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, CULE);
1770 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1771 Ftintrz_uw_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1772 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1773 return true;
1774 }
1775 case kExprI32SConvertSatF64:
1776 ftintrz_w_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1777 movfr2gr_s(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1778 return true;
1779 case kExprI32UConvertSatF64: {
1780 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1781 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1782 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1783 CompareF64(src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, CULE);
1784 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1785 Ftintrz_uw_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1786 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1787 return true;
1788 }
1789 case kExprI64SConvertSatF32:
1790 ftintrz_l_s(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1791 movfr2gr_d(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1792 return true;
1793 case kExprI64UConvertSatF32: {
1794 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1795 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1796 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<float>(0.0));
1797 CompareF32(src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, CULE);
1798 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1799 Ftintrz_ul_s(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1800 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1801 return true;
1802 }
1803 case kExprI64SConvertSatF64:
1804 ftintrz_l_d(kScratchDoubleReg, src.fp());
1805 movfr2gr_d(dst.gp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1806 return true;
1807 case kExprI64UConvertSatF64: {
1808 Label isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero;
1809 mov(dst.gp(), zero_reg);
1810 MacroAssembler::Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<double>(0.0));
1811 CompareF64(src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg, CULE);
1812 BranchTrueShortF(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1813 Ftintrz_ul_d(dst.gp(), src.fp(), kScratchDoubleReg);
1814 bind(&isnan_or_lessthan_or_equal_zero);
1815 return true;
1816 }
1817 default:
1818 return false;
1819 }
1820}

1852
1853void LiftoffAssembler::emit_cond_jump(Condition cond, Label* label,
1854 ValueKind kind, Register lhs,
1855 Register rhs,
1856 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
1857 if (rhs == no_reg) {
1858 if (kind == kI32) {
1859 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1860 Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
1861 slli_w(scratch0, lhs, 0);
1862 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, scratch0, Operand(zero_reg));
1863 } else {
1864 DCHECK(kind == kI64);
1865 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(zero_reg));
1866 }
1867 } else {
1868 if (kind == kI64) {
1869 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(rhs));
1870 } else {
1871 DCHECK((kind == kI32) || (kind == kRtt) || (kind == kRef) ||
1872 (kind == kRefNull));
1873 MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(rhs));
1874 }
1875 }
1876}

1878void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_cond_jumpi(Condition cond, Label* label,
1879 Register lhs, int32_t imm,
1880 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
1881 MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(imm));
1882}

1884void LiftoffAssembler::emit_ptrsize_cond_jumpi(Condition cond, Label* label,
1885 Register lhs, int32_t imm,
1886 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
1887 MacroAssembler::Branch(label, cond, lhs, Operand(imm));
1888}

1895void LiftoffAssembler::emit_i32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
1896 Register lhs, Register rhs) {
1897 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1898 Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
1899 Register scratch1 = kScratchReg;
1900
1901 slli_w(scratch0, lhs, 0);
1902 slli_w(scratch1, rhs, 0);
1903
1904 CompareWord(cond, dst, scratch0, Operand(scratch1));
1905}

1915}

1917namespace liftoff {
1918
1919inline FPUCondition ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(Condition condition,
1920 bool* predicate) {
1921 switch (condition) {
1922 case kEqual:
1923 *predicate = true;
1924 return CEQ;
1925 case kNotEqual:
1926 *predicate = false;
1927 return CEQ;
1928 case kUnsignedLessThan:
1929 *predicate = true;
1930 return CLT;
1931 case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
1932 *predicate = false;
1933 return CLT;
1934 case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
1935 *predicate = true;
1936 return CLE;
1937 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
1938 *predicate = false;
1939 return CLE;
1940 default:
1941 *predicate = true;
1942 break;
1943 }
1944 UNREACHABLE();
1945}
1946
1947} // namespace liftoff
1948
1949void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f32_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
1950 DoubleRegister lhs,
1951 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1952 Label not_nan, cont;
1953 MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF32(lhs, rhs);
1954 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);
1955 // If one of the operands is NaN, return 1 for f32.ne, else 0.
1956 if (cond == ne) {
1957 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
1958 } else {
1959 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
1960 }
1961 MacroAssembler::Branch(&cont);
1962
1963 bind(&not_nan);
1964
1965 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
1966 bool predicate;
1967 FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
1968 MacroAssembler::CompareF32(lhs, rhs, fcond);
1969 if (predicate) {
1970 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);
1971 } else {
1972 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfFPUCondition(dst);
1973 }
1974
1975 bind(&cont);
1976}
1977
1978void LiftoffAssembler::emit_f64_set_cond(Condition cond, Register dst,
1979 DoubleRegister lhs,
1980 DoubleRegister rhs) {
1981 Label not_nan, cont;
1982 MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF64(lhs, rhs);
1983 MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(&not_nan);
1984 // If one of the operands is NaN, return 1 for f64.ne, else 0.
1985 if (cond == ne) {
1986 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
1987 } else {
1988 MacroAssembler::Move(dst, zero_reg);
1989 }
1990 MacroAssembler::Branch(&cont);
1991
1992 bind(&not_nan);
1993
1994 MacroAssembler::li(dst, 1);
1995 bool predicate;
1996 FPUCondition fcond = liftoff::ConditionToConditionCmpFPU(cond, &predicate);
1997 MacroAssembler::CompareF64(lhs, rhs, fcond);
1998 if (predicate) {
1999 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfNotFPUCondition(dst);
2000 } else {
2001 MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfFPUCondition(dst);
2002 }
2003
2004 bind(&cont);
2005}

2014void LiftoffAssembler::emit_smi_check(Register obj, Label* target,
2015 SmiCheckMode mode,
2016 const FreezeCacheState& frozen) {
2017 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2018 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2019 And(scratch, obj, Operand(kSmiTagMask));
2020 Condition condition = mode == kJumpOnSmi ? eq : ne;
2021 Branch(target, condition, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
2022}

3379
3380void LiftoffAssembler::StackCheck(Label* ool_code) {
3381 Register limit_address = kScratchReg;
3382 LoadStackLimit(limit_address, StackLimitKind::kInterruptStackLimit);
3383 Branch(ool_code, ule, sp, Operand(limit_address));
3384}
3385
3386void LiftoffAssembler::AssertUnreachable(AbortReason reason) {
3387 MacroAssembler::AssertUnreachable(reason);
3388}
3389
3390void LiftoffAssembler::PushRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3391 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3392 unsigned num_gp_regs = gp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3393 if (num_gp_regs) {
3394 unsigned offset = num_gp_regs * kSystemPointerSize;
3395 addi_d(sp, sp, -offset);
3396 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3397 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3398 offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
3399 St_d(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3400 gp_regs.clear(reg);
3401 }
3402 DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
3403 }
3404 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3405 unsigned num_fp_regs = fp_regs.GetNumRegsSet();
3406 if (num_fp_regs) {
3407 unsigned slot_size = 8;
3408 addi_d(sp, sp, -(num_fp_regs * slot_size));
3409 unsigned offset = 0;
3410 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3411 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3412 MacroAssembler::Fst_d(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, offset));
3413 fp_regs.clear(reg);
3414 offset += slot_size;
3415 }
3416 DCHECK_EQ(offset, num_fp_regs * slot_size);
3417 }
3418}
3419
3420void LiftoffAssembler::PopRegisters(LiftoffRegList regs) {
3421 LiftoffRegList fp_regs = regs & kFpCacheRegList;
3422 unsigned fp_offset = 0;
3423 while (!fp_regs.is_empty()) {
3424 LiftoffRegister reg = fp_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
3425 MacroAssembler::Fld_d(reg.fp(), MemOperand(sp, fp_offset));
3426 fp_regs.clear(reg);
3427 fp_offset += 8;
3428 }
3429 if (fp_offset) addi_d(sp, sp, fp_offset);
3430 LiftoffRegList gp_regs = regs & kGpCacheRegList;
3431 unsigned gp_offset = 0;
3432 while (!gp_regs.is_empty()) {
3433 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_regs.GetLastRegSet();
3434 Ld_d(reg.gp(), MemOperand(sp, gp_offset));
3435 gp_regs.clear(reg);
3436 gp_offset += kSystemPointerSize;
3437 }
3438 addi_d(sp, sp, gp_offset);
3439}
3440
3441void LiftoffAssembler::RecordSpillsInSafepoint(
3442 SafepointTableBuilder::Safepoint& safepoint, LiftoffRegList all_spills,
3443 LiftoffRegList ref_spills, int spill_offset) {
3444 LiftoffRegList fp_spills = all_spills & kFpCacheRegList;
3445 int spill_space_size = fp_spills.GetNumRegsSet() * kSimd128Size;
3446 LiftoffRegList gp_spills = all_spills & kGpCacheRegList;
3447 while (!gp_spills.is_empty()) {
3448 LiftoffRegister reg = gp_spills.GetFirstRegSet();
3449 if (ref_spills.has(reg)) {
3450 safepoint.DefineTaggedStackSlot(spill_offset);
3451 }
3452 gp_spills.clear(reg);
3453 ++spill_offset;
3454 spill_space_size += kSystemPointerSize;
3455 }
3456 // Record the number of additional spill slots.
3457 RecordOolSpillSpaceSize(spill_space_size);
3458}
3459
3460void LiftoffAssembler::DropStackSlotsAndRet(uint32_t num_stack_slots) {
3461 DCHECK_LT(num_stack_slots,
3462 (1 << 16) / kSystemPointerSize); // 16 bit immediate
3463 Drop(static_cast<int>(num_stack_slots));
3464 Ret();
3465}
3466
3467void LiftoffAssembler::CallCWithStackBuffer(
3468 const std::initializer_list<VarState> args, const LiftoffRegister* rets,
3469 ValueKind return_kind, ValueKind out_argument_kind, int stack_bytes,
3470 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
3471 addi_d(sp, sp, -stack_bytes);
3472
3473 int arg_offset = 0;
3474 for (const VarState& arg : args) {
3475 liftoff::StoreToMemory(this, MemOperand{sp, arg_offset}, arg);
3476 arg_offset += value_kind_size(arg.kind());
3477 }
3478 DCHECK_LE(arg_offset, stack_bytes);
3479
3480 // Pass a pointer to the buffer with the arguments to the C function.
3481 // On LoongArch, the first argument is passed in {a0}.
3482 constexpr Register kFirstArgReg = a0;
3483 mov(kFirstArgReg, sp);
3484
3485 // Now call the C function.
3486 constexpr int kNumCCallArgs = 1;
3487 PrepareCallCFunction(kNumCCallArgs, kScratchReg);
3488 CallCFunction(ext_ref, kNumCCallArgs);
3489
3490 // Move return value to the right register.
3491 const LiftoffRegister* next_result_reg = rets;
3492 if (return_kind != kVoid) {
3493 constexpr Register kReturnReg = a0;
3494#ifdef USE_SIMULATOR
3495 // When calling a host function in the simulator, if the function returns an
3496 // int32 value, the simulator does not sign-extend it to int64 because in
3497 // the simulator we do not know whether the function returns an int32 or
3498 // an int64. So we need to sign extend it here.
3499 if (return_kind == kI32) {
3500 slli_w(next_result_reg->gp(), kReturnReg, 0);
3501 } else if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
3502 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
3503 }
3504#else
3505 if (kReturnReg != next_result_reg->gp()) {
3506 Move(*next_result_reg, LiftoffRegister(kReturnReg), return_kind);
3507 }
3508#endif
3509 ++next_result_reg;
3510 }
3511
3512 // Load potential output value from the buffer on the stack.
3513 if (out_argument_kind != kVoid) {
3514 liftoff::Load(this, *next_result_reg, MemOperand(sp, 0), out_argument_kind);
3515 }
3516
3517 addi_d(sp, sp, stack_bytes);
3518}
3519
3520void LiftoffAssembler::CallC(const std::initializer_list<VarState> args_list,
3521 ExternalReference ext_ref) {
3522 // First, prepare the stack for the C call.
3523 const int num_args = static_cast<int>(args_list.size());
3524 PrepareCallCFunction(num_args, kScratchReg);
3525
3526 // Note: If we ever need more than eight arguments we would need to load the
3527 // stack arguments to registers (via LoadToRegister), then push them to the
3528 // stack.
3529
3530 // Execute the parallel register move for register parameters.
3531 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(kCArgRegs), num_args);
3532 const VarState* const args = args_list.begin();
3533 ParallelMove parallel_move{this};
3534 for (int reg_arg = 0; reg_arg < num_args; ++reg_arg) {
3535 parallel_move.LoadIntoRegister(LiftoffRegister{kCArgRegs[reg_arg]},
3536 args[reg_arg]);
3537 }
3538 parallel_move.Execute();
3539
3540 // Now call the C function.
3541 CallCFunction(ext_ref, num_args);
3542}

3552void LiftoffAssembler::CallIndirect(const ValueKindSig* sig,
3553 compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3554 Register target) {
3555 // For loong64, we have more cache registers than wasm parameters. That means
3556 // that target will always be in a register.
3557 DCHECK(target.is_valid());
3558 CallWasmCodePointer(target, call_descriptor->signature_hash());
3559}

3562 compiler::CallDescriptor* call_descriptor, Register target) {
3563 DCHECK(target.is_valid());
3564 CallWasmCodePointer(target, call_descriptor->signature_hash(),
3565 CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
3566}

3570 // patched at relocation.

3572}

3585void LiftoffAssembler::emit_store_nonzero_if_nan(Register dst, FPURegister src,
3586 ValueKind kind) {
3587 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3588 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3589 Label not_nan;
3590 if (kind == kF32) {
3591 CompareIsNanF32(src, src);
3592 } else {
3593 DCHECK_EQ(kind, kF64);
3594 CompareIsNanF64(src, src);
3595 }
3596 BranchFalseShortF(&not_nan);
3597 li(scratch, 1);
3598 St_w(scratch, MemOperand(dst, 0));
3599 bind(&not_nan);
3600}

3613
3614void LiftoffStackSlots::Construct(int param_slots) {
3615 DCHECK_LT(0, slots_.size());
3616 SortInPushOrder();
3617 int last_stack_slot = param_slots;
3618 for (auto& slot : slots_) {
3619 const int stack_slot = slot.dst_slot_;
3620 int stack_decrement = (last_stack_slot - stack_slot) * kSystemPointerSize;
3621 DCHECK_LT(0, stack_decrement);
3622 last_stack_slot = stack_slot;
3623 const LiftoffAssembler::VarState& src = slot.src_;
3624 switch (src.loc()) {
3625 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kStack:
3626 if (src.kind() != kS128) {
3627 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
3628 asm_->Ld_d(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
3629 asm_->Push(kScratchReg);
3630 } else {
3631 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSimd128Size);
3632 asm_->Ld_d(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_ - 8));
3633 asm_->Push(kScratchReg);
3634 asm_->Ld_d(kScratchReg, liftoff::GetStackSlot(slot.src_offset_));
3635 asm_->Push(kScratchReg);
3636 }
3637 break;
3638 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kRegister: {
3639 int pushed_bytes = SlotSizeInBytes(slot);
3640 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - pushed_bytes);
3641 liftoff::push(asm_, src.reg(), src.kind());
3642 break;
3643 }
3644 case LiftoffAssembler::VarState::kIntConst: {
3645 asm_->AllocateStackSpace(stack_decrement - kSystemPointerSize);
3646 asm_->li(kScratchReg, Operand(src.i32_const()));
3647 asm_->Push(kScratchReg);
3648 break;
3649 }
3650 }
3651 }
3652}
